When debug printing a `std::string` while a certain custom iomanip is used, then string should be cut in the middle, replacing that part with `" ...(N chars)... "`, where N is the integral value of the number of removed characters. If N is less than 20 then print the full string instead. This should work for code like: `Dout(dc::notice, maxlen(100) << str);`.  See `utils/iomanip.h` lines 99 to 128 for usage example of `utils::iomanip::Sticky`.
